{
  "video_id": "PLk8Pm_XBJE",
  "title": "How we'll become cyborgs and extend human potential | Hugh Herr",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 13388.0,
      "end_time": 15574.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m an MIT professor,"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 15598.0,
      "end_time": 18574.0,
      "text": "but I do not design buildings or computer systems."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 18938.0,
      "end_time": 21415.0,
      "text": "Rather, I build body parts,"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 22133.0,
      "end_time": 25157.0,
      "text": "bionic legs that augment human walking and running."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 25812.0,
      "end_time": 28745.0,
      "text": "In 1982, I was in a mountain-climbing accident,"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 28769.0,
      "end_time": 32403.0,
      "text": "and both of my legs had to be amputated due to tissue damage from frostbite."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 33245.0,
      "end_time": 35181.0,
      "text": "Here, you can see my legs:"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 35206.0,
      "end_time": 40506.0,
      "text": "24 sensors, six microprocessors and muscle-tendon-like actuators."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 40530.0,
      "end_time": 43399.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m basically a bunch of nuts and bolts from the knee down."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 43846.0,
      "end_time": 46202.0,
      "text": "But with this advanced bionic technology,"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 46226.0,
      "end_time": 48468.0,
      "text": "I can skip, dance and run."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 50138.0,
      "end_time": 51181.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 51206.0,
      "end_time": 52357.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 52381.0,
      "end_time": 54991.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 55150.0,
      "end_time": 58944.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m a bionic man, but I&#39;m not yet a cyborg."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 62284.0,
      "end_time": 65860.0,
      "text": "When I think about moving my legs,"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 65110.0,
      "end_time": 68229.0,
      "text": "neural signals from my central nervous system"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 68253.0,
      "end_time": 69872.0,
      "text": "pass through my nerves"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 69896.0,
      "end_time": 73700.0,
      "text": "and activate muscles within my residual limbs."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 75380.0,
      "end_time": 78390.0,
      "text": "Artificial electrodes sense these signals,"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 78630.0,
      "end_time": 80528.0,
      "text": "and small computers in the bionic limb"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 80552.0,
      "end_time": 84575.0,
      "text": "decode my nerve pulses into my intended movement patterns."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 86493.0,
      "end_time": 88393.0,
      "text": "Stated simply,"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 88418.0,
      "end_time": 89749.0,
      "text": "when I think about moving,"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 89773.0,
      "end_time": 93970.0,
      "text": "that command is communicated to the synthetic part of my body."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 94466.0,
      "end_time": 98244.0,
      "text": "However, those computers can&#39;t input information into my nervous system."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 98838.0,
      "end_time": 101726.0,
      "text": "When I touch and move my synthetic limbs,"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 101751.0,
      "end_time": 105400.0,
      "text": "I do not experience normal touch and movement sensations."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 106108.0,
      "end_time": 110144.0,
      "text": "If I were a cyborg and could feel my legs"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 111255.0,
      "end_time": 115800.0,
      "text": "via small computers inputting information into my nervous system,"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 115105.0,
      "end_time": 117463.0,
      "text": "it would fundamentally change, I believe,"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 117487.0,
      "end_time": 120231.0,
      "text": "my relationship to my synthetic body."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 120605.0,
      "end_time": 122430.0,
      "text": "Today, I can&#39;t feel my legs,"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 123788.0,
      "end_time": 124970.0,
      "text": "and because of that,"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 124994.0,
      "end_time": 128439.0,
      "text": "my legs are separate tools from my mind and my body."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 128463.0,
      "end_time": 129845.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re not part of me."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 131480.0,
      "end_time": 134766.0,
      "text": "I believe that if I were a cyborg and could feel my legs,"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 134790.0,
      "end_time": 137218.0,
      "text": "they would become part of me, part of self."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 137923.0,
      "end_time": 142680.0,
      "text": "At MIT, we&#39;re thinking about NeuroEmbodied Design."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 142920.0,
      "end_time": 143869.0,
      "text": "In this design process,"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 145110.0,
      "end_time": 150573.0,
      "text": "the designer designs human flesh and bone, the biological body itself,"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 150597.0,
      "end_time": 155534.0,
      "text": "along with synthetics to enhance the bidirectional communication"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 155558.0,
      "end_time": 158400.0,
      "text": "between the nervous system and the built world."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 159406.0,
      "end_time": 163795.0,
      "text": "NeuroEmbodied Design is a methodology to create cyborg function."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 165843.0,
      "end_time": 170194.0,
      "text": "In this design process, designers contemplate a future"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 170218.0,
      "end_time": 173369.0,
      "text": "in which technology no longer compromises separate,"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 173393.0,
      "end_time": 176321.0,
      "text": "lifeless tools from our minds and our bodies,"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 176345.0,
      "end_time": 180171.0,
      "text": "a future in which technology has been carefully integrated"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 180195.0,
      "end_time": 181766.0,
      "text": "within our nature,"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 181790.0,
      "end_time": 184965.0,
      "text": "a world in which what is biological and what is not,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 184989.0,
      "end_time": 187750.0,
      "text": "what is human and what is not,"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 187990.0,
      "end_time": 189155.0,
      "text": "what is nature and what is not"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 189180.0,
      "end_time": 191367.0,
      "text": "will be forever blurred."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 191391.0,
      "end_time": 194867.0,
      "text": "That future will provide humanity new bodies."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 196156.0,
      "end_time": 198895.0,
      "text": "NeuroEmbodied Design will extend our nervous systems"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 198919.0,
      "end_time": 200593.0,
      "text": "into the synthetic world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 200617.0,
      "end_time": 203930.0,
      "text": "and the synthetic world into us,"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 203117.0,
      "end_time": 205767.0,
      "text": "fundamentally changing who we are."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 206994.0,
      "end_time": 210480.0,
      "text": "By designing the biological body to better communicate"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 210720.0,
      "end_time": 211859.0,
      "text": "with the built design world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 213800.0,
      "end_time": 216650.0,
      "text": "humanity will end disability in this 21st century"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 216890.0,
      "end_time": 219639.0,
      "text": "and establish the scientific and technological basis"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 219663.0,
      "end_time": 220964.0,
      "text": "for human augmentation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 221937.0,
      "end_time": 226394.0,
      "text": "extending human capability beyond innate, physiological levels,"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 226418.0,
      "end_time": 229544.0,
      "text": "cognitively, emotionally and physically."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 230218.0,
      "end_time": 234450.0,
      "text": "There are many ways in which to build new bodies across scale,"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 234474.0,
      "end_time": 238418.0,
      "text": "from the biomolecular to the scale of tissues and organs."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 238443.0,
      "end_time": 241649.0,
      "text": "Today, I want to talk about one area of NeuroEmbodied Design,"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 241673.0,
      "end_time": 245737.0,
      "text": "in which the body&#39;s tissues are manipulated and sculpted"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 245761.0,
      "end_time": 248307.0,
      "text": "using surgical and regenerative processes."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 250331.0,
      "end_time": 251966.0,
      "text": "The current amputation paradigm"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 251991.0,
      "end_time": 256580.0,
      "text": "hasn&#39;t changed fundamentally since the US Civil War"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 256820.0,
      "end_time": 259836.0,
      "text": "and has grown obsolete in light of dramatic advancements"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 259860.0,
      "end_time": 263796.0,
      "text": "in actuators, control systems and neural interfacing technologies."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 265580.0,
      "end_time": 269336.0,
      "text": "A major deficiency is the lack of dynamic muscle interactions"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 269360.0,
      "end_time": 271502.0,
      "text": "for control and proprioception."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 272682.0,
      "end_time": 274532.0,
      "text": "What is proprioception?"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 274556.0,
      "end_time": 277794.0,
      "text": "When you flex your ankle, muscles in the front of your leg contract,"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 277818.0,
      "end_time": 280794.0,
      "text": "simultaneously stretching muscles in the back of your leg."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 280818.0,
      "end_time": 283303.0,
      "text": "The opposite happens when you extend your ankle."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 283327.0,
      "end_time": 285559.0,
      "text": "Here, muscles in the back of your leg contract,"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 285583.0,
      "end_time": 287304.0,
      "text": "stretching muscles in the front."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 287328.0,
      "end_time": 289304.0,
      "text": "When these muscles flex and extend,"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 289328.0,
      "end_time": 291662.0,
      "text": "biological sensors within the muscle tendons"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 291686.0,
      "end_time": 294162.0,
      "text": "send information through nerves to the brain."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 294186.0,
      "end_time": 296789.0,
      "text": "This is how we&#39;re able to feel where our feet are"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 296814.0,
      "end_time": 299360.0,
      "text": "without seeing them with our eyes."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 300186.0,
      "end_time": 304409.0,
      "text": "The current amputation paradigm breaks these dynamic muscle relationships,"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 304433.0,
      "end_time": 308529.0,
      "text": "and in so doing eliminates normal proprioceptive sensations."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 308553.0,
      "end_time": 311292.0,
      "text": "Consequently, a standard artificial limb"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 311316.0,
      "end_time": 313991.0,
      "text": "cannot feed back information into the nervous system"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 314150.0,
      "end_time": 316759.0,
      "text": "about where the prosthesis is in space."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 316783.0,
      "end_time": 319940.0,
      "text": "The patient therefore cannot sense and feel"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 319964.0,
      "end_time": 322931.0,
      "text": "the positions and movements of the prosthetic joint"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 322955.0,
      "end_time": 325500.0,
      "text": "without seeing it with their eyes."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 326153.0,
      "end_time": 330970.0,
      "text": "My legs were amputated using this Civil War-era methodology."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 330626.0,
      "end_time": 333181.0,
      "text": "I can feel my feet, I can feel them right now"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 333206.0,
      "end_time": 335650.0,
      "text": "as a phantom awareness."
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 335890.0,
      "end_time": 336978.0,
      "text": "But when I try to move them, I cannot."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 337200.0,
      "end_time": 339748.0,
      "text": "It feels like they&#39;re stuck inside rigid ski boots."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 340730.0,
      "end_time": 341886.0,
      "text": "To solve these problems,"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 341910.0,
      "end_time": 346948.0,
      "text": "at MIT, we invented the agonist-antagonist myoneural interface,"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 346972.0,
      "end_time": 348805.0,
      "text": "or AMI, for short."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 348829.0,
      "end_time": 352463.0,
      "text": "The AMI is a method to connect nerves within the residuum"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 352487.0,
      "end_time": 354710.0,
      "text": "to an external, bionic prosthesis."
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 355405.0,
      "end_time": 358500.0,
      "text": "How is the AMI designed, and how does it work?"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 359508.0,
      "end_time": 363170.0,
      "text": "The AMI comprises two muscles that are surgically connected,"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 363410.0,
      "end_time": 365358.0,
      "text": "an agonist linked to an antagonist."
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 365909.0,
      "end_time": 368707.0,
      "text": "When the agonist contracts upon electrical activation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 368732.0,
      "end_time": 371224.0,
      "text": "it stretches the antagonist."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 371248.0,
      "end_time": 373530.0,
      "text": "This muscle dynamic interaction"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 373554.0,
      "end_time": 376585.0,
      "text": "causes biological sensors within the muscle tendon"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 376610.0,
      "end_time": 380790.0,
      "text": "to send information through the nerve to the central nervous system,"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 380103.0,
      "end_time": 384707.0,
      "text": "relating information on the muscle tendon&#39;s length, speed and force."
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 384731.0,
      "end_time": 387490.0,
      "text": "This is how muscle tendon proprioception works,"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 387730.0,
      "end_time": 389715.0,
      "text": "and it&#39;s the primary way we, as humans,"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 389740.0,
      "end_time": 393866.0,
      "text": "can feel and sense the positions, movements and forces on our limbs."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 394386.0,
      "end_time": 395688.0,
      "text": "When a limb is amputated,"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 395712.0,
      "end_time": 399832.0,
      "text": "the surgeon connects these opposing muscles within the residuum"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 399856.0,
      "end_time": 401730.0,
      "text": "to create an AMI."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 401970.0,
      "end_time": 404190.0,
      "text": "Now, multiple AMI constructs can be created"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 404214.0,
      "end_time": 408175.0,
      "text": "for the control and sensation of multiple prosthetic joints."
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 408199.0,
      "end_time": 411597.0,
      "text": "Artificial electrodes are then placed on each AMI muscle,"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 411621.0,
      "end_time": 415272.0,
      "text": "and small computers within the bionic limb decode those signals"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 415296.0,
      "end_time": 418207.0,
      "text": "to control powerful motors on the bionic limb."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 418933.0,
      "end_time": 421930.0,
      "text": "When the bionic limb moves,"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 421117.0,
      "end_time": 422974.0,
      "text": "the AMI muscles move back and forth,"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 422998.0,
      "end_time": 425190.0,
      "text": "sending signals through the nerve to the brain,"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 425214.0,
      "end_time": 429356.0,
      "text": "enabling a person wearing the prosthesis to experience natural sensations"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 429380.0,
      "end_time": 431864.0,
      "text": "of positions and movements of the prosthesis."
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 432492.0,
      "end_time": 436626.0,
      "text": "Can these tissue-design principles be used in an actual human being?"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 437786.0,
      "end_time": 441595.0,
      "text": "A few years ago, my good friend Jim Ewing -- of 34 years --"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 441619.0,
      "end_time": 443341.0,
      "text": "reached out to me for help."
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 444272.0,
      "end_time": 446328.0,
      "text": "Jim was in an a terrible climbing accident."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 446352.0,
      "end_time": 449490.0,
      "text": "He fell 50 feet in the Cayman Islands"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 449740.0,
      "end_time": 452272.0,
      "text": "when his rope failed to catch him hitting the ground&#39;s surface."
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 453339.0,
      "end_time": 455809.0,
      "text": "He suffered many, many injuries:"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 455833.0,
      "end_time": 459470.0,
      "text": "punctured lungs and many broken bones."
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 460600.0,
      "end_time": 463790.0,
      "text": "After his accident, he dreamed of returning to his chosen sport"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 463814.0,
      "end_time": 465118.0,
      "text": "of mountain climbing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 465142.0,
      "end_time": 467190.0,
      "text": "but how might this be possible?"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 469322.0,
      "end_time": 471544.0,
      "text": "The answer was Team Cyborg,"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 472369.0,
      "end_time": 475608.0,
      "text": "a team of surgeons, scientists and engineers"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 475632.0,
      "end_time": 480474.0,
      "text": "assembled at MIT to rebuild Jim back to his former climbing prowess."
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 480498.0,
      "end_time": 484554.0,
      "text": "Team member Dr. Matthew Carty amputated Jim&#39;s badly damaged leg"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 484578.0,
      "end_time": 486690.0,
      "text": "at Brigham and Women&#39;s Hospital in Boston,"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 486714.0,
      "end_time": 488786.0,
      "text": "using the AMI surgical procedure."
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 489262.0,
      "end_time": 492667.0,
      "text": "Tendon pulleys were created and attached to Jim&#39;s tibia bone"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 492691.0,
      "end_time": 494729.0,
      "text": "to reconnect the opposing muscles."
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 495460.0,
      "end_time": 498364.0,
      "text": "The AMI procedure reestablished the neural link"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 498389.0,
      "end_time": 501264.0,
      "text": "between Jim&#39;s ankle-foot muscles and his brain."
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 501854.0,
      "end_time": 504418.0,
      "text": "When Jim moves his phantom limb,"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 504442.0,
      "end_time": 507450.0,
      "text": "the reconnected muscles move in dynamic pairs,"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 507474.0,
      "end_time": 511911.0,
      "text": "causing signals of proprioception to pass through nerves to the brain,"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 511935.0,
      "end_time": 515554.0,
      "text": "so Jim experiences normal sensations with ankle-foot positions and movements,"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 515578.0,
      "end_time": 516895.0,
      "text": "even when blindfolded."
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 517842.0,
      "end_time": 521279.0,
      "text": "Here&#39;s Jim at the MIT laboratory after his surgeries."
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 521303.0,
      "end_time": 524423.0,
      "text": "We electrically linked Jim&#39;s AMI muscles, via the electrodes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 524447.0,
      "end_time": 525605.0,
      "text": "to a bionic limb,"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 525629.0,
      "end_time": 528390.0,
      "text": "and Jim quickly learned how to move the bionic limb"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 528414.0,
      "end_time": 531318.0,
      "text": "in four distinct ankle-foot movement directions."
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 532000.0,
      "end_time": 535630.0,
      "text": "We were excited by these results, but then Jim stood up,"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 535870.0,
      "end_time": 537953.0,
      "text": "and what occurred was truly remarkable."
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 537977.0,
      "end_time": 541992.0,
      "text": "All the natural biomechanics mediated by the central nervous system"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 542170.0,
      "end_time": 545366.0,
      "text": "emerged via the synthetic limb"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 545390.0,
      "end_time": 548905.0,
      "text": "as an involuntary, reflexive action."
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 548929.0,
      "end_time": 552826.0,
      "text": "All the intricacies of foot placement during stair ascent --"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 552850.0,
      "end_time": 556348.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 556372.0,
      "end_time": 558276.0,
      "text": "emerged before our eyes."
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 559644.0,
      "end_time": 561469.0,
      "text": "Here&#39;s Jim descending steps,"
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 561493.0,
      "end_time": 564485.0,
      "text": "reaching with his bionic toe to the next stair tread,"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 564509.0,
      "end_time": 567250.0,
      "text": "automatically exhibiting natural motions"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 567490.0,
      "end_time": 569841.0,
      "text": "without him even trying to move his limb."
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 569865.0,
      "end_time": 574478.0,
      "text": "Because Jim&#39;s central nervous system is receiving the proprioceptive signals,"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 574502.0,
      "end_time": 578549.0,
      "text": "it knows exactly how to control the synthetic limb in a natural way."
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 579635.0,
      "end_time": 585222.0,
      "text": "Now, Jim moves and behaves as if the synthetic limb is part of him."
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 585746.0,
      "end_time": 587706.0,
      "text": "For example, one day in the lab,"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 587730.0,
      "end_time": 590826.0,
      "text": "he accidentally stepped on a roll of electrical tape."
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 590850.0,
      "end_time": 593477.0,
      "text": "Now, what do you do when something&#39;s stuck to your shoe?"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 593501.0,
      "end_time": 596112.0,
      "text": "You don&#39;t reach down like this; it&#39;s way too awkward."
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 596136.0,
      "end_time": 597430.0,
      "text": "Instead, you shake it off,"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 597454.0,
      "end_time": 599279.0,
      "text": "and that&#39;s exactly what Jim did"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 599303.0,
      "end_time": 602469.0,
      "text": "after being neurally connected to the limb for just a few hours."
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 603436.0,
      "end_time": 605413.0,
      "text": "What was most interesting to me"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 605437.0,
      "end_time": 608305.0,
      "text": "is what Jim was telling us he was experiencing."
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 608329.0,
      "end_time": 611654.0,
      "text": "He said, \"The robot became part of me.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 612217.0,
      "end_time": 616200.0,
      "text": "Jim Ewing: The morning after the first time I was attached to the robot,"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 616270.0,
      "end_time": 621393.0,
      "text": "my daughter came downstairs and asked me how it felt to be a cyborg,"
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 621417.0,
      "end_time": 625386.0,
      "text": "and my answer was that I didn&#39;t feel like a cyborg."
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 625410.0,
      "end_time": 629236.0,
      "text": "I felt like I had my leg,"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 629260.0,
      "end_time": 633981.0,
      "text": "and it wasn&#39;t that I was attached to the robot"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 634500.0,
      "end_time": 636626.0,
      "text": "so much as the robot was attached to me,"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 636650.0,
      "end_time": 638182.0,
      "text": "and the robot became part of me."
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 638206.0,
      "end_time": 640697.0,
      "text": "It became my leg pretty quickly."
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 641617.0,
      "end_time": 642767.0,
      "text": "Hugh Herr: Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 642792.0,
      "end_time": 645880.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 645904.0,
      "end_time": 649277.0,
      "text": "By connecting Jim&#39;s nervous system bidirectionally"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 649301.0,
      "end_time": 651710.0,
      "text": "to his synthetic limb,"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 651950.0,
      "end_time": 654190.0,
      "text": "neurological embodiment was achieved."
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 654430.0,
      "end_time": 659520.0,
      "text": "I hypothesized that because Jim can think and move his synthetic limb,"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 659544.0,
      "end_time": 663853.0,
      "text": "and because he can feel those movements within his nervous system,"
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 663878.0,
      "end_time": 667500.0,
      "text": "the prosthesis is no longer a separate tool,"
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 667290.0,
      "end_time": 671425.0,
      "text": "but an integral part of Jim, an integral part of his body."
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 672108.0,
      "end_time": 676106.0,
      "text": "Because of this neurological embodiment, Jim doesn&#39;t feel like a cyborg."
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 677215.0,
      "end_time": 679432.0,
      "text": "He feels like he just has his leg back,"
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 679456.0,
      "end_time": 681300.0,
      "text": "that he has his body back."
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 681580.0,
      "end_time": 682731.0,
      "text": "Now I&#39;m often asked"
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 682755.0,
      "end_time": 686311.0,
      "text": "when I&#39;m going to be neurally linked to my synthetic limbs bidirectionally,"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 686335.0,
      "end_time": 688119.0,
      "text": "when I&#39;m going to become a cyborg."
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 688143.0,
      "end_time": 690906.0,
      "text": "The truth is, I&#39;m hesitant to become a cyborg."
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 691966.0,
      "end_time": 695173.0,
      "text": "Before my legs were amputated, I was a terrible student."
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 695197.0,
      "end_time": 698200.0,
      "text": "I got D&#39;s and often F&#39;s in school."
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 698440.0,
      "end_time": 700773.0,
      "text": "Then, after my limbs were amputated,"
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 700797.0,
      "end_time": 702896.0,
      "text": "I suddenly became an MIT professor."
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 703353.0,
      "end_time": 705520.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 705544.0,
      "end_time": 709266.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 709290.0,
      "end_time": 713766.0,
      "text": "Now I&#39;m worried that once I&#39;m neurally connected to my limbs once again,"
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 713791.0,
      "end_time": 717481.0,
      "text": "my brain will remap back to its not-so-bright self."
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 717505.0,
      "end_time": 718807.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 718831.0,
      "end_time": 722902.0,
      "text": "But you know what, that&#39;s OK, because at MIT, I already have tenure."
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 722926.0,
      "end_time": 724554.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 724578.0,
      "end_time": 727443.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 727467.0,
      "end_time": 729824.0,
      "text": "I believe the reach of NeuroEmbodied Design"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 729849.0,
      "end_time": 732706.0,
      "text": "will extend far beyond limb replacement"
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 732730.0,
      "end_time": 735434.0,
      "text": "and will carry humanity into realms"
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 735458.0,
      "end_time": 738148.0,
      "text": "that fundamentally redefine human potential."
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 738866.0,
      "end_time": 740585.0,
      "text": "In this 21st century,"
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 740609.0,
      "end_time": 745460.0,
      "text": "designers will extend the nervous system into powerfully strong exoskeletons"
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 745700.0,
      "end_time": 749277.0,
      "text": "that humans can control and feel with their minds."
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 750139.0,
      "end_time": 753282.0,
      "text": "Muscles within the body can be reconfigured"
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 753306.0,
      "end_time": 756219.0,
      "text": "for the control of powerful motors,"
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 756243.0,
      "end_time": 760347.0,
      "text": "and to feel and sense exoskeletal movements,"
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 760371.0,
      "end_time": 764132.0,
      "text": "augmenting humans&#39; strength, jumping height and running speed."
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 764807.0,
      "end_time": 769457.0,
      "text": "In this 21st century, I believe humans will become superheroes."
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 770313.0,
      "end_time": 773924.0,
      "text": "Humans may also extend their bodies"
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 773948.0,
      "end_time": 776939.0,
      "text": "into non-anthropomorphic structures, such as wings,"
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 777805.0,
      "end_time": 781835.0,
      "text": "controlling and feeling each wing movement within the nervous system."
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 782716.0,
      "end_time": 786110.0,
      "text": "Leonardo da Vinci said, \"When once you have tasted flight,"
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 786134.0,
      "end_time": 789661.0,
      "text": "you will forever walk the earth with your eyes turned skyward,"
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 789685.0,
      "end_time": 794351.0,
      "text": "for there you have been and there you will always long to return.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 795490.0,
      "end_time": 797530.0,
      "text": "During the twilight years of this century,"
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 797554.0,
      "end_time": 801784.0,
      "text": "I believe humans will be unrecognizable in morphology and dynamics"
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 801808.0,
      "end_time": 803761.0,
      "text": "from what we are today."
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 803785.0,
      "end_time": 806719.0,
      "text": "Humanity will take flight and soar."
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 807695.0,
      "end_time": 810997.0,
      "text": "Jim Ewing fell to earth and was badly broken,"
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 811210.0,
      "end_time": 814401.0,
      "text": "but his eyes turned skyward, where he always longed to return."
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 815281.0,
      "end_time": 817837.0,
      "text": "After his accident, he not only dreamed to walk again,"
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 817861.0,
      "end_time": 820725.0,
      "text": "but also to return to his chosen sport of mountain climbing."
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 821657.0,
      "end_time": 826395.0,
      "text": "At MIT, Team Cyborg built Jim a specialized limb for the vertical world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 826419.0,
      "end_time": 830649.0,
      "text": "a brain-controlled leg with full position and movement sensations."
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 832650.0,
      "end_time": 835288.0,
      "text": "Using this technology, Jim returned to the Cayman Islands,"
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 835312.0,
      "end_time": 837219.0,
      "text": "the site of his accident,"
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 837243.0,
      "end_time": 841251.0,
      "text": "rebuilt as a cyborg to climb skyward once again."
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 841275.0,
      "end_time": 843520.0,
      "text": "(Crashing waves)"
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 867727.0,
      "end_time": 874727.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 883578.0,
      "end_time": 884728.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 884753.0,
      "end_time": 888334.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 888358.0,
      "end_time": 891819.0,
      "text": "Ladies and gentlemen, Jim Ewing, the first cyborg rock climber."
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 891843.0,
      "end_time": 898843.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}